const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Do I need a Facebook Business page for my flat roofing firm?",
    answer: "A Facebook Business page is required for the Messenger integration — personal profiles cannot connect. Flat roofers posting GRP transformation galleries, EPDM installation sequences, and topcoat close-up shots attract engagement from homeowners actively comparing their leaking felt to your professionally finished fibreglass."
  },
  {
    question: "What flat roofing enquiries come through Messenger?",
    answer: "Predominantly homeowners frustrated with leaking repairs and builders needing extension waterproofing. Homeowners message about persistent felt leaks, ponding, and GRP blister repairs. Builders message about deck-ready extension roofs needing GRP, EPDM, or single-ply installation. Each sender has reviewed your flat roof portfolio and identified your firm as capable of the waterproofing quality they require."
  },
  {
    question: "How fast does the AI reply to flat roof messages?",
    answer: "Replies reach the sender within seconds of the message landing. Facebook's active indicator shows your flat roofing firm is immediately available. Homeowners messaging about rainfall dripping through their extension ceiling during a storm need an instant response that acknowledges the urgency and asks the right diagnostic questions about system type and leak location."
  },
  {
    question: "What does Messenger cost for flat roofing firms?",
    answer: `Messenger is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as a channel add-on. A domestic GRP flat roof generates £1,500 to £4,000 in revenue. One homeowner's complete GRP replacement — captured through a prompt Messenger reply to a rainy evening leak panic while competing firms' messages accumulated — covers the channel cost for the foreseeable future.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I continue Messenger conversations personally?",
    answer: "Post one reply in any Messenger thread and the AI steps aside for good. Most flat roofers let the AI capture the initial details — roof system, failure type, area, insulation needs, and programme — then follow up to arrange the site measurement, discuss system options, and provide the quotation."
  },
  {
    question: "How is Messenger data from flat roofing queries protected?",
    answer: "All Messenger conversations, roof condition photographs, property locations, system specifications, and sender contact information are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Data goes exclusively to you. No roof specifications reach competing flat roofers, are shared with membrane suppliers, or are available to any third party."
